Safely Guiding the Immune System to Fight Disease

Eradivir is developing drugs that bind to infected cells, serving as a beacon to guide the immune system.

A new paradigm in drug delivery.

Much like precision guided munitions, our patented drug delivery technology applies medicine to the specific sites in the body where it is needed. This improves efficacy, reduces side effects, and lowers required dosage.

Our Company

One Technology, Many Viruses

By leveraging our company's targeting molecule, our technology allows a mix and match approach, clipping in virus-specific moieties late in synthesis to allow adaptation to a wide variety of infections. This has allowed us to develop a deep pipeline of potent drug candidates that bind to a variety of exosites unique to a number of prominent viral infections.
Learn More about Targeted Viral Therapy

A Different Approach to Influenza

Our lead drug has been shown to be more effective than the current standard of care against all strains of influenza. Our compounds links the inhibitor zanamivir, which binds to all forms of influenza neuraminidase to two antibody recruiting molecules that in turn recruit an immune response on infected cells.
